:title("TypeScript to LLVM IR compiler") ;
:description("Compiles TypeScript to an LLVM IR module and runs it with the built-in IR
interpreter.

TypeScript is JavaScript with an erased static type layer, so this is the JavaScript
compiler (see js-to-llvm-ir.abnf) widened to accept - and then throw away - the type
syntax: ': Type' annotations, generic '<T>' parameter lists, 'as Type' casts (identity),
non-null '!' assertions and optional '?' markers are all parsed and dropped. An interface
and a 'type' alias are pure type declarations and emit nothing. An 'enum' of bare names
becomes an object of integer constants (Color.Red === 0). Everything runtime is exactly
JavaScript.

The language is exactly the one of typescript-interpreter.abnf; see there for a
description (including the bitwise operators and assignment targets that reach through
calls). Unlike MetaJS, variables are NOT type pinned: declarations and assignments go
through the UNPINNED scope externals js_scope_decl / js_scope_set / js_scope_get, so a
variable can hold values of any type over its lifetime.

The emitted IR is handle threaded code: every dynamic value is an i64 handle into the
value table of the Go side JS runtime (abnf/jsrt.go), and every operation with real
JS semantics is a call to one of its js_* externals (js_add, js_get, js_call, ...).
Only the control flow is real IR: if/while/for/&&/||/?: compile to basic blocks,
branches and phis, driven by js_truthy. The handles 0..3 are the constants undefined,
null, false and true. Variables live in scope chain objects on the host side
(js_scope_new, js_scope_get, and the declaring/assigning js_scope_decl/js_scope_set),
and the scope chain is what gives closures their captured
environment: a function expression becomes an own IR function jsf_N(env, args) plus a
js_closure(N, currentScope) at the site of its creation. String and number literals
enter through module globals (js_str_mem) and js_num_i/js_num_str.

Every tag composes a small code generator function (a 'thunk') out of the thunks of its
children. Expression thunks get the current basic block and return {b: endBlock,
v: handle value}; statement thunks get the current block and return the block that the
following code has to continue in (short circuit operators and loops branch, so both
can move the insertion point). The top level becomes the function jsmain(env, args),
which runs the program statements and then calls main().

The exit code of the metacompiler run is the value that main() returns, so the test
programs are self checking: they return 0 on success.
The same language with the same semantics is interpreted directly by typescript-interpreter.abnf.

A plain `=` assignment to a name that was never declared becomes an implicit global
(created in the root scope) through js_scope_set_or_create, matching the non-strict
JavaScript semantics of typescript-interpreter.abnf. A compound assignment (+=, ++, ...) reads
the old value first and so still requires a prior var/let/const declaration.") ;


// --- main rules

// Shared token productions (languages/lib).
:include("lib/cstyle-comments.abnf") ;
:include("lib/ident-dollar.abnf") ;
:include("lib/dq-strings.abnf") ;
:include("lib/numbers.abnf") ;
:include("lib/bools.abnf") ;

:startRule(Program) ;
:whitespace(Whitespace) ;

// The merged statement thunks of the top level become jsmain(env, args) in the module.
Program     <~~ buildMain(takeAll()) ~~>
            = { Statement } ;

// Every statement production pushes exactly one thunk: function() -> undefined | signal.
// The TypeScript-only declarations (interface / type alias / enum) come first, before
// VarDecl, so 'const enum' is not misread as a 'const' variable named 'enum'.
Statement   <~~ push(stmtPos(pop())) ~~>
            = Block | ImportDecl | ExportDecl | NamespaceDecl | DecoratedDecl | Interface | TypeAlias | EnumDecl | ClassDecl | TryStmt | Destructure
            | GenFuncDecl | AsyncFuncDecl | VarDecl | If | While | Do | ForOf | For | Switch | Return | Break | Continue
            | Throw | FuncDecl | DebuggerStmt | Empty | ExprStmt ;

// --- TypeScript module system (import / export) and namespaces. ---
// The module specifier is handed to resolveImport (core.importFile): a specifier that
// names a project file ('import { Vec } from "./geomlib"' -> geomlib.ts, searched under
// the program's directory and the -i roots) is parsed with this grammar and its top-level
// declarations are stashed (importDepth > 0) and prepended to jsrun, so they run before
// the main file's; the named binding list is cosmetic. A specifier that names no project
// file is recognized but not implemented (abort by default, warn+ignore under
// -warn-unsupported), the old behavior. The import statement itself emits nothing (a
// no-op statement thunk). export in front of a real declaration is a transparent prefix:
// the inner class/function/var/type is compiled genuinely (the 'export' is erased); the
// value-less export forms (export {..}, export * from, export =, export default <expr>)
// are accepted and not-implemented.
ImportDecl  <~~ resolveImport(importSpec(takeAll()), up.pos); push(function(b) { return b }) ~~>
            = KwImport ( ImportEquals | ImportBare | ImportTypeOnly | ImportFull ) ;
ImportBare  = ImportPath [ ";" ] ;
ImportEquals = Id "=" Id "(" ImportPath ")" [ ";" ] ;
ImportTypeOnly = KwType ImportClause KwFrom ImportPath [ ";" ] ;
ImportFull  = ImportClause KwFrom ImportPath [ ";" ] ;
ImportClause = ImportDefault [ "," ( ImportNS | ImportNamed ) ] | ImportNS | ImportNamed ;
ImportDefault = Id ;
ImportNS    = "*" KwAs Id ;
ImportNamed = "{" [ ImportSpec { "," ImportSpec } [ "," ] ] "}" ;
ImportSpec  = [ KwType ] ( Id | StringLit ) [ KwAs Id ] ;
// The module specifier of an import: the same double/single quoted literal as StringLit,
// but it pushes the DECODED PATH TEXT (a plain string, not a value thunk) so the
// ImportDecl tag can hand it to resolveImport. The mid-rule tag position that captures the
// inner content is identical to DqString/SqString (languages/lib/dq-strings.abnf).
ImportPath  = DqPath | SqPath ;
DqPath      = '"' :whitespace() { StrEsc | DqPlain } <~~ push(unescapeJs(up.in)) ~~> '"' :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
SqPath      = "'" :whitespace() { StrEsc | SqPlain } <~~ push(unescapeJs(up.in)) ~~> "'" :whitespace(Whitespace) ;

// export: a declaration keeps compiling (the keyword is dropped); the value-less forms
// notImpl. ExportBody delegates to the ordinary declaration productions, whose thunk
// lands directly on the Statement frame (ExportDecl adds no frame of its own).
ExportDecl  = KwExport [ KwDefault ] ExportBody ;
ExportBody  = ClassDecl | GenFuncDecl | AsyncFuncDecl | FuncDecl | VarDecl | EnumDecl | Interface | TypeAlias
            | ExportStar | ExportClause | ExportAssign | ExportDefaultExpr ;
ExportStar  <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplStmt("re-export (export *)", up.pos)) ~~>
            = "*" [ KwAs Id ] KwFrom StringLit [ ";" ] ;
ExportClause <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplStmt("export clause", up.pos)) ~~>
            = "{" [ ExportSpec { "," ExportSpec } [ "," ] ] "}" [ KwFrom StringLit ] [ ";" ] ;
ExportSpec  = [ KwType ] ( Id | StringLit ) [ KwAs ( Id | StringLit ) ] ;
ExportAssign <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplStmt("export assignment (export =)", up.pos)) ~~>
            = "=" AssignExpr [ ";" ] ;
ExportDefaultExpr <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplStmt("export default expression", up.pos)) ~~>
            = AssignExpr [ ";" ] ;

// namespace / module / declare - the whole ambient/namespace body is skipped.
NamespaceDecl <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplStmt("namespace / module declaration", up.pos)) ~~>
            = [ KwDeclare ] ( KwNamespace | KwModule | KwGlobal ) [ NamespaceName ] SkipBlock ;
NamespaceName = Id { "." Id } | StringLit ;

// A decorator (@Component, @Injectable(...)) is parsed and its effect not implemented;
// the decorated class/declaration itself is still compiled (its thunk is repushed).
DecoratedDecl <~~ notImpl("decorator", up.pos); push(pop()) ~~>
            = Decorator { Decorator } ( ExportDecl | ClassDecl ) ;
Decorator   = "@" Id { "." Id } [ SkipParen ] ;

// async / generator function declarations are accepted structurally but not implemented
// (there is no event loop / iterator protocol); their bodies are skipped.
AsyncFuncDecl <~~ push(notImplStmt("async function", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwAsync KwFunction [ "*" ] Id [ TypeParams ] SkipParen [ TypeAnnot ] SkipBlock ;
GenFuncDecl <~~ push(notImplStmt("generator function", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwFunction "*" Id [ TypeParams ] SkipParen [ TypeAnnot ] SkipBlock ;

DebuggerStmt <~~ push(function(b) { return b }) ~~>
            = KwDebugger [ ";" ] ;

// --- TypeScript type-only declarations. ---
// An interface and a type alias exist only in the type layer; they emit nothing (a
// no-op statement thunk that returns its block unchanged).
Interface   <~~ push(function(b) { return b }) ~~>
            = KwInterface Id [ TypeParams ] [ KwExtends TypeList ] SkipBlock ;
TypeAlias   <~~ push(function(b) { return b }) ~~>
            = KwType Id [ TypeParams ] "=" Type [ ";" ] ;

// An enum of bare names becomes an object binding: enum Color { Red, Green, Blue }
// declares Color = {Red:0, Green:1, Blue:2}. Explicit integer values are honored and
// the auto-increment continues from the last value. The same {name: value} pairs are
// computed here as in the interpreter, so the two engines agree.
EnumDecl    <~~ push(makeEnum(takeAll())) ~~>
            = [ "const" KwEnd ] KwEnum Id <~~ push({enumName: up.in}) ~~>
              "{" [ EnumMember { "," EnumMember } [ "," ] ] "}" [ ";" ] ;
EnumMember  <~~ push(makeEnumMember(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Id <~~ push({mname: up.in}) ~~> [ "=" EnumVal ] ;
EnumVal     <~~ push({val: parseInt(up.in)}) ~~>
            = ( "0" | "1"..."9" ) :whitespace() { "0"..."9" } :whitespace(Whitespace) ;

// The JS switch: === comparison, fallthrough until break, stacked labels, default
// anywhere. The body is a flat list - the labels must be tried before Statement,
// because 'case 1:' would otherwise parse as two expression statements (semicolons
// are optional).
Switch      <~~ push(makeSwitch(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwSwitch "(" Expression ")" "{" { CaseLabel | DefaultLabel | Statement } "}" ;
CaseLabel   <~~ push({casev: pop()}) ~~>
            = KwCase AssignExpr ":" ;
DefaultLabel <~~ push({isdflt: true}) ~~>
            = KwDefault ":" ;

Block       <~~ push(makeBlockStmt(takeAll())) ~~>
            = "{" { Statement } "}" ;

// var, let and const all declare a block scoped variable in the current scope.
VarDecl     = VarDeclCore [ ";" ] ;
VarDeclCore <~~ push(makeSeq(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwVar Declarator { "," Declarator } ;
// The optional ': Type' annotation is parsed and erased (pushes nothing).
Declarator  <~~ push(makeDecl(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ TypeAnnot ] [ "=" AssignExpr ] ;

// [condThunk, thenThunk] or [condThunk, thenThunk, elseThunk].
If          <~~ push(makeIf(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwIf "(" Expression ")" Statement [ KwElse Statement ] ;

While       <~~ push(makeWhile(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = KwWhile "(" Expression ")" Statement ;

Do          <~~ push(makeDo(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = KwDo Statement KwWhile "(" Expression ")" [ ";" ] ;

// The three optional parts are wrapped with a kind marker, otherwise e.g.
// 'for (;c;)' and 'for (i=0;;)' could not be told apart on the stack.
For         <~~ push(makeFor(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwFor "(" [ ForInit ] ";" [ ForCond ] ";" [ ForPost ] ")" Statement ;
ForInit     <~~ push({k:"init", t:pop()}) ~~> = ForVar | ForExpr ;
ForVar      = VarDeclCore ;
ForExpr     <~~ push(exprToClause(pop())) ~~> = Expression ;
ForCond     <~~ push({k:"cond", t:pop()}) ~~> = Expression ;
ForPost     <~~ push({k:"post", t:exprToClause(pop())}) ~~> = Expression ;

// [] or [exprThunk].
Return      <~~ push(makeReturn(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwReturn [ Expression ] [ ";" ] ;

Break       <~~ push(makeBreak()) ~~>
            = KwBreak [ ";" ] ;

Continue    <~~ push(makeContinue()) ~~>
            = KwContinue [ ";" ] ;

Throw       <~~ push(makeThrow(pop())) ~~>
            = KwThrow Expression [ ";" ] ;

// A function declaration binds the closure in the current scope when it executes.
// The generic parameter list '<T>', the parameter type annotations and the return
// type are all parsed and erased; only the parameter names survive.
FuncDecl    <~~ push(makeFuncDecl(pop(), pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = KwFunction Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ TypeParams ] ParamList [ TypeAnnot ] Block ;

ParamList   <~~ push(takeAll()) /* Collect the parameter names into one array. */ ~~>
            = "(" [ TSParam { "," TSParam } [ "," ] ] ")" ;
// A parameter: a plain name, a rest parameter (...xs, bound to the first rest argument),
// or a destructuring pattern (not implemented, bound to a hidden placeholder name). The
// optional '?' marker, ': Type' annotation and '= default' initializer are erased; only
// the name reaches the closure machinery.
TSParam     = { Decorator } ( RestParam | DestructParam | NormalParam ) ;
NormalParam = Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ "?" ] [ TypeAnnot ] [ ParamDefault ] ;
RestParam   = "..." Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ "?" ] [ TypeAnnot ] ;
DestructParam <~~ notImpl("destructuring parameter", up.pos); push("0destructured") ~~>
            = DPattern [ "?" ] [ TypeAnnot ] [ ParamDefault ] ;
ParamDefault <~~ pop() ~~> = "=" AssignExpr ;

Empty       <~~ push(function(b) { return b }) ~~>
            = ";" ;

ExprStmt    <~~ push(exprToStmt(pop())) ~~>
            = Expression [ ";" ] ;

// Every expression production pushes exactly one thunk: function(block) -> {b, v}.
Expression  = AssignExpr ;

// Assignment is an expression and associates to the right: a = b = c.
// If the assignment shape does not fit (e.g. 'a == b'), the parser falls back to CondExpr.
AssignExpr  = Assignment | CondExpr ;
Assignment  <~~ push(makeAssign(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Target ( "+=" | "-=" | "*=" | "/=" | "%=" | "<<=" | ">>>=" | ">>=" | "&=" | "^=" | "|=" | "=" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> AssignExpr ;

// An assignable place: a variable, or a member path that may reach through calls
// but must end in a member: findScope(name)[name] = value.
// The local stack holds [name, suffix marker, suffix marker, ...].
Target      <~~ push(makeTargetRef(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> { CallSuffix | DotSuffix | IndexSuffix } ;

CondExpr    <~~ push(makeCond(takeAll())) ~~>
            = NullishExpr [ "?" AssignExpr ":" AssignExpr ] ;

// The nullish coalescing operator (a ?? b) sits just above ||. It is accepted but not
// implemented (it needs a null/undefined test the runtime does not expose as an
// operator); the left operand is kept so the expression still yields a value.
NullishExpr <~~ push(makeNiFold(takeAll(), up.pos, "nullish coalescing (??)")) ~~>
            = OrExpr { "??" OrExpr } ;

OrExpr      <~~ push(makeOrAnd(takeAll(), true)) ~~>
            = AndExpr { "||" AndExpr } ;

AndExpr     <~~ push(makeOrAnd(takeAll(), false)) ~~>
            = BitOrExpr { "&&" BitOrExpr } ;

// The bitwise levels sit between && and equality, like in JS. A single "|" that
// actually starts a "||" fails its right side, the iteration rolls back, and the
// enclosing || level picks it up.
BitOrExpr   <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = BitXorExpr { "|" <~~ push("|") ~~> BitXorExpr } ;
BitXorExpr  <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = BitAndExpr { "^" <~~ push("^") ~~> BitAndExpr } ;
BitAndExpr  <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = EqExpr { "&" <~~ push("&") ~~> EqExpr } ;

// The longer operators must be tried before their prefixes ("===" before "==").
EqExpr      <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = RelExpr { ( "===" | "!==" | "==" | "!=" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> RelExpr } ;

RelExpr     <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = InstExpr { ( "<=" | ">=" | "<" | ">" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> InstExpr } ;

// instanceof and in are relational operators; neither is exposed as a runtime primitive,
// so they are accepted and not implemented (the left operand is kept as the value).
InstExpr    <~~ push(makeNiFold(takeAll(), up.pos, "instanceof / in operator")) ~~>
            = ShiftExpr { ( KwInstanceof | KwIn ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ShiftExpr } ;

ShiftExpr   <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = AddExpr { ( "<<" | ">>>" | ">>" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> AddExpr } ;

AddExpr     <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = MulExpr { ( "+" | "-" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> MulExpr } ;

MulExpr     <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = ExpExpr { ( "*" | "/" | "%" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ExpExpr } ;

// Exponentiation (a ** b) binds tighter than * / %. It is accepted but not implemented
// (no exponent runtime primitive); the left operand is kept as the value.
ExpExpr     <~~ push(makeNiFold(takeAll(), up.pos, "exponentiation (**)")) ~~>
            = UnaryExpr { "**" UnaryExpr } ;

UnaryExpr   = PreIncDec | Neg | Not | BitNot | Typeof | Await | Delete | Void | Yield | PostfixExpr ;
// await / delete / void are accepted but not implemented; the operand is still evaluated.
Await       <~~ push(makeNiUnary(pop(), up.pos, "await")) ~~>
            = KwAwait UnaryExpr ;
Delete      <~~ push(makeNiUnary(pop(), up.pos, "delete")) ~~>
            = KwDelete UnaryExpr ;
Void        <~~ push(makeNiUnary(pop(), up.pos, "void")) ~~>
            = KwVoid UnaryExpr ;
// yield / yield* only occur in generators, which are not implemented; the result is undefined.
Yield       <~~ push(makeYield(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwYield [ "*" ] [ AssignExpr ] ;
// Prefix ++/--: the expression value is the new one.
PreIncDec   <~~ push(makePreIncDec(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = ( "++" | "--" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> Target ;
Neg         <~~ push(makeUnary(pop(), "js_neg")) ~~>
            = "-" UnaryExpr ;
Not         <~~ push(makeUnary(pop(), "js_not")) ~~>
            = "!" UnaryExpr ;
BitNot      <~~ push(makeBitNot(pop())) ~~>
            = "~" UnaryExpr ;
Typeof      <~~ push(makeUnary(pop(), "js_typeof")) ~~>
            = KwTypeof UnaryExpr ;

// The postfix forms: i++ evaluates to the old value.
PostfixExpr = IncDec | SuperCall | CallMember ;
IncDec      <~~ push(makeIncDec(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Target ( "++" | "--" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ;

// super(args) delegates to the parent constructor; super.m(args) invokes the parent's
// method on 'this'. popName pulls the optional '.m' out, leaving the argument thunks.
SuperCall   <~~ push(makeSuperCall(popName(), takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwSuper [ "." Id <~~ push({mname: up.in}) ~~> ] "(" [ Arg { "," Arg } [ "," ] ] ")" ;

// A primary expression followed by any mix of calls and member accesses: a.b[i](x).c().
// A call after a member access is a method call: the object becomes 'this' of the callee.
// The 'as Type' cast and the postfix non-null '!' are type-layer only: they push
// nothing and so are transparent to foldCallMember (identity at run time). The '!'
// carries a negative lookahead so it is never stolen from the '!=' / '!==' operators.
CallMember  <~~ push(foldCallMember(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Primary { CallSuffix | DotSuffix | IndexSuffix | OptDot | OptIndex | OptCall | NonNullSuffix | AsCast } ;
CallSuffix  <~~ push({kind:"call", args: takeAll()}) ~~>
            = "(" [ Arg { "," Arg } [ "," ] ] ")" ;
// A call argument, allowing the spread form f(...xs). Spread is accepted but not
// implemented; the spread operand is passed as a single argument.
Arg         = Spread | AssignExpr ;
Spread      <~~ notImpl("spread / rest argument (...)", up.pos); push(pop()) ~~>
            = "..." AssignExpr ;
DotSuffix   = "." Id <~~ push({kind:"member", key: makeConst(up.in)}) ~~> ;
IndexSuffix <~~ push({kind:"member", key: pop()}) ~~>
            = "[" Expression "]" ;
// Optional chaining (a?.b, a?.[i], a?.(x)) is accepted but not implemented; it is lowered
// as an ordinary member/index/call, so a null/undefined receiver still throws.
OptDot      <~~ notImpl("optional chaining (?.)", up.pos); push({kind:"member", key: makeConst(pop())}) ~~>
            = "?." Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ;
OptIndex    <~~ notImpl("optional chaining (?.[])", up.pos); push({kind:"member", key: pop()}) ~~>
            = "?." "[" Expression "]" ;
OptCall     <~~ notImpl("optional call (?.())", up.pos); push({kind:"call", args: takeAll()}) ~~>
            = "?." "(" [ Arg { "," Arg } [ "," ] ] ")" ;
NonNullSuffix = "!" !"=" ;
AsCast      = KwAs Type ;

Primary     = AsyncArrow | ArrowFn | NewExpr | RegexLit | "(" Expression ")" | FunctionExpr | TemplateLit | ObjectLit | ArrayLit | StringLit | NumberLit
            | True | False | Null | Undefined | VarRef ;

// An async arrow function (async x => x, async () => {...}) is accepted but not
// implemented; async function expressions are handled by FunctionExpr's KwAsync prefix.
AsyncArrow  <~~ push(makeNiArrow(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwAsync ArrowParams "=>" ArrowBody ;

// new C(args) | new C<T>(args): build an instance of the class named C. The generic
// type arguments are erased. Member/call suffixes may follow (new C().m()).
NewExpr     <~~ push(makeNew(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwNew Id <~~ push({cls: up.in}) ~~> [ TypeArgs ] [ "(" [ Arg { "," Arg } [ "," ] ] ")" ] ;

// The optional name of a function expression is accepted but not bound; generics and
// the return type are erased.
FunctionExpr <~~ push(makeFunctionExpr(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = [ KwAsync ] KwFunction [ "*" ] [ Id ] [ TypeParams ] ParamList [ TypeAnnot ] Block ;

// A trailing comma before the closing brace/bracket is allowed (idiomatic TypeScript).
// Members: an object method or spread (both not implemented) are tried before the
// key:value pair and the shorthand form ({x} === {x: x}).
ObjectLit   <~~ push(makeObject(takeAll())) ~~>
            = "{" [ ObjMember { "," ObjMember } [ "," ] ] "}" ;
ObjMember   = ObjSpread | ObjMethod | PropDef | ShorthandProp ;
PropDef     <~~ push(makeProp(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = PropKey ":" AssignExpr ;
// A computed key ({[expr]: v}) pushes the key thunk; makeProp already accepts a thunk key.
PropKey     = Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> | StringLit | ComputedKey ;
ComputedKey = "[" AssignExpr "]" ;
// Shorthand: { x } binds the property x to the variable x.
ShorthandProp <~~ push(makeProp(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = Id <~~ push(up.in); push(makeVarRef(up.in)) ~~> ;
// An object method ({ m() {..} }) and object spread ({ ...o }) are not implemented; the
// member contributes nothing to the object.
ObjMethod   <~~ notImpl("object method", up.pos); takeAll() ~~>
            = [ "get" KwEnd | "set" KwEnd | "async" KwEnd | "*" ] PropKey ParamList [ TypeAnnot ] Block ;
ObjSpread   <~~ notImpl("object spread (...)", up.pos); takeAll() ~~>
            = "..." AssignExpr ;

ArrayLit    <~~ push(makeArray(takeAll())) ~~>
            = "[" [ ArrElem { "," ArrElem } [ "," ] ] "]" ;
ArrElem     = Spread | AssignExpr ;

// Arrow functions: x => x+1, (a, b) => a+b, () => { ... }. They reuse the same
// closure machinery (emitFunction/js_closure) as function expressions; an expression
// body is an implicit 'return <expr>'. Tried before "(" Expression ")" and VarRef.
ArrowFn     <~~ push(makeArrow(takeAll())) ~~>
            = ArrowParams "=>" ArrowBody ;
// The parenthesized form may carry typed parameters and a return type; the single-Id
// form is untyped. Both push only the parameter names.
ArrowParams <~~ push({aparams: takeAll()}) ~~>
            = "(" [ TSParam { "," TSParam } ] ")" [ TypeAnnot ]
            | Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ;
ArrowBody   = ArrowBlock | ArrowExpr ;
ArrowBlock  <~~ push({body: pop()}) ~~>  = Block ;
ArrowExpr   <~~ push({ebody: pop()}) ~~> = AssignExpr ;

// Template literals: `text ${expr} more`. Each ${...} is evaluated and coerced to
// string (js_add); the result is always a string. Whitespace is disabled inside the
// backticks and re-enabled inside a ${...}. A lone '$' is a literal character.
TemplateLit <~~ push(makeTemplate(takeAll())) ~~>
            = "`" :whitespace() { TplExpr | TplChars | TplDollar } "`" :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
TplExpr     <~~ push({expr: pop()}) ~~>
            = "${" :whitespace(Whitespace) Expression "}" ;
TplChars    <~~ push({str: unescapeJs(up.in)}) ~~>
            = TplChar { TplChar } ;
TplChar     = TplEsc | TplPlain ;
TplEsc      = "\\" "\x00"..."\U0010ffff" ;
TplPlain    = "\x00"..."\x23" | "\x25"..."\x5b" | "\x5d"..."\x5f" | "\x61"..."\U0010ffff" ;
TplDollar   <~~ push({str: "$"}) ~~>
            = "$" ;

// for-of over an array or string iterates its elements/characters (genuine).
// for-in is not implemented (host key enumeration is an off-limits extern);
// under -warn-unsupported its iterable is evaluated and the body skipped.
ForOf       <~~ push(makeForOf(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwFor "(" [ KwVar ] Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~>
              ( KwOf | KwIn ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> Expression ")" Statement ;

// A destructuring binding is accepted but not lowered; the initializer still runs.
Destructure <~~ push(makeDestructure(pop(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwVar DPattern "=" AssignExpr [ ";" ] ;
DPattern    = "[" [ DElem { "," DElem } ] "]" | "{" [ DField { "," DField } ] "}" ;
DElem       = Id | DPattern ;
DField      = Id [ ":" DElem ] ;

// try/catch/finally and throw are implemented: throw calls js_throw, each try/catch/
// finally body compiles to its own closure handed to js_try, and a return/break/
// continue leaving a try or catch body becomes a control signal that excDispatch
// re-issues in the enclosing frame. The catch binding is optional (ES2019 catch {}).
TryStmt     <~~ push(makeTry(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwTry TryBody [ CatchClause ] [ FinallyClause ] ;
TryBody     <~~ push({trybody: pop()}) ~~>
            = Block ;
CatchClause <~~ push(makeCatch(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwCatch [ "(" Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ ":" Type ] ")" ] Block ;
FinallyClause <~~ push({finbody: pop()}) ~~>
            = KwFinally Block ;

// A class declaration: fields, a constructor and instance/static methods lower to the
// shared __class machinery (an instance is js_obj_new carrying a __class descriptor that
// holds the methods; a method call dispatches through js_mcall, super through
// js_supercall). Access modifiers and every type annotation - generic parameter lists,
// field/return/param types, the implements clause - are parsed and erased.
ClassDecl   <~~ push(makeClassStmt(takeAll())) ~~>
            = [ "abstract" KwEnd ] KwClass Id <~~ push({cname: up.in}); curClassName = up.in ~~> [ TypeParams ]
              [ KwExtends Id <~~ push({ext: up.in}) ~~> [ TypeArgs ] ]
              [ KwImplements TypeList ]
              "{" { ClassMember } "}" ;

